 The last days of Akinwunmi Ambode as the governor of Lagos State were indeed humiliating to say the least. So humbling was it that the chubby checked and dark-complexioned man stylishly avoided his successor’s inauguration. Simply put, Ambode was the lab rat used to test the prototype of a one-term governor, having been the first-ever in Lagos State. Said to be set to bounce back to reckoning as a minister by virtue of his supposed closeness to President Muhammadu Buhari and his work in Lagos State, his cronies bragged about his return without a doubt. Ambode’s hope was however dashed when his name was conspicuously missing from a list of 43 individuals nominated and sent to the Senate by the President for ministerial appointment. The post No Respite For Akinwunmi Ambode  Source: Independent Despite losing out of the All Progressives governorship ticket, the Lagos State Governor, Akinwunmi Ambode has won his polling unit for the re-election of President Muhammadu Buhari. At the polling unit where Ambode voted in Epe, Lagos State, APC polled 131 votes, while the People's Democratic Party polled 116 votes… February 23, 2019 In "News" Governor Akinwunmi Ambode of Lagos State on Saturday expressed sadness over the demise of the first executive President of Nigeria, Alhaji Shehu Shagari. Shagari, who was the first and only President of Nigeriaâ€™s Second Republic from1979 to 1983, died on Friday in Abuja at the age of 93. Ambode, in… December 30, 2018 In "News" The Lagos State Governor, Akinwunmi Ambode, has said former President Goodluck Jonathan denied his state ecological fund due to “political consideration.” He said this at a sensitisation workshop on water technology and environmental control exhibition and conference (WATEC), in the state. Ambode also noted though his government was willing to… July 12, 2017 In "News"